      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not even about the \"practical steps\" anymore. i've been staring at the numbers for hours and there's literally no math that makes this work. it's a black hole. i feel like a ghost. i walk around and people look at me and they don't know that i'm basically a dead man walking. the shame is just... it's constant. every time i breathe it's like i'm failing again. i just want the noise to stop. i just want everything to be quiet and for this feeling to finally go away.",
